[3] Cholera - Nigeria
Date: Fri 7 Nov 2014
Source: Vaccine News Daily [edited]
http://vaccinenewsdaily.com/africa/332048-nigerian-cholera-outbreak-rises-to-34008-infections/


The number of cases from the ongoing outbreak of cholera in Nigeria climbed to 34 008 as of 12 Oct 2014, the National Travel Health Network and Centre reported on Wed 5 Nov 2014. Since the outbreak began in May 2013, 664 cholera-related fatalities have been reported.

Cholera is spread through contaminated water or food as a result of poor sanitation, meaning areas with weaker sanitation systems are more likely to see cases. Person-to-person transmission of cholera is rare.

Cases have been reported in 19 states, including Adamawa, Bauchi, Borno, Kaduna, Kano, Katsina, Kebbi, Plateau, and Zamfara.

