[4] Cholera - India (Gujarat State)
Date: Wed 12 Nov 2014
Source: The Indian Express [edited]
http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/ahmedabad/gujarat-sankheda-declared-cholera-hit/


Two persons died and over 300 were taken ill after drinking contaminated water from a government overhead tank. The taluka [administrative division] Chhota Udepur district in Gujarat, has been declared cholera hit after tests showed strains of the disease. A 28 year old and a 35 year old died on [12 Nov 2014]. People started complaining of diarrhea, vomiting, and headache since 7.30 pm Tuesday evening [11 Nov 2014], and as reports came in nearly 352 had taken ill. Of these, 40 are at the referral hospital and 30 have been taken to Vadodara. There was panic after rumors that a monkey had died in the overhead tank that was supplying water to the town. Regional deputy director, health, Dr PB Itare told The Indian Express, "This is a cholera outbreak. The monkey bit is not true. The contamination has happened during transmission via pipeline." Tankers have been deployed to provide drinking water as an interim arrangement.

[Byline: Aditi Raja]

